Hi, the other day at my skool was the book fair. I got 2 books, CLICK HERE and DARE TO BE SCARED? I am almost finished with CLICK HERE and I only got it yesterday. It is such a great book. Probably, my second of first favorite. WOW! I can't believe I might choose it over the Notebook. NAH! Well, Maybe. I will tell you what the book is about: It's basically about this girl surviving 7th grade and her private blog {like this, AKA a live journal} that she only reads, ends up on her skool website and it has all her secrets. This is what the back of the book says:

Seventh-grader Erin Swift has a talent for computers, a love for Snickers,and big feet that are great for soccer but useless for dancing. She has a lot on her mind: a new school where she and her best friend, Jilly are seperated for the first time into different units; a crush on the Cute Boy in her homeroom;the task of leading the school intranet project; and a role as a corncob in the school play. Then real disaster strikes, and Erin sets off on a surprising journey to self-discovery-- and the many meanings of cherry-flavored Tootsie Pops. 

It really is awesome. On the cover, there's a computer mouse, converse chuck taylor shoes {my favorite brand of sneakers/shoes},a skool bus, a soccer ball, and a mouth full of braces eating a lolipop. It is basically a girl book. I recommend that girls only read it.LOL, I read Kyle part and we cracked up laughing.
I have been editing and editing my live journal but sooner or later, it will be perfect!

I am talking always and away like usual to friends and to my family! Yeah today was okay I guess. We had health but I missed it because of Editorial Board,we were making posters and the teacher gave us cookies{oreos}. Also today during 8th period we had this thing called "Mix it up" and what we did was every person got a different number from each homeroom in 6th grade. All of us met in the cafe and we sat at our number given table and then our homeroom teachers gave us bags of food and we would dump them into the bowl in the center of our table. We filled out this sheet about ourselves and now tomorrow we have assigned seats to sit with those people. I know its confusing but have a nice day! Really please do!!!
